  "texts": [
    "It also shows that a socialscience-guided taxonomy can breach AI safety guardrails with minimal algorithmic design, which lays the groundwork for potential future advancements toward efficiency and efficacy.",
    "As the interaction pattern between everyday users and LLMs evolves, these risks are likely to increase, which highlights the urgency for continued research and discussion around such overlooked vulnerability rooted in human-like communication.",
    "Responsible Disclosure.",
    "We have disclosed our findings to Meta and OpenAI prior to publication and discuss ethical considerations in Section 9.",
    "As LLMs become more widely used in real-world applications, jailbreak research efforts have diversified and can be broadly classified into 3 main categories: Optimization, Side-channel Communication, and Distribution-based methods."
